      "content": "A drawing on paper (176 x 303 mm) by **Hendrick Avercamp** (Amsterdam, 1585 – Kampen, 1634), dated c. 1605–1634, depicting a winter landscape scene with figures on ice: four figures around a frozen boat (foreground left), kolf players (center), a man with an axe (right bank), a farmhouse (middle left), and a village in the background. Executed in pencil, pen in black, watercolor wash, and white heightening. Monogrammed \"HA.\" Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
